From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0020/N] prefetch_bsd_aarch64: stub Prefetch::read/write under CHERI

The aarch64 `prfm` instruction with `[reg, reg]` (register+register
offset) form is not supported in Morello capability mode — the
purecap assembler rejects it with `index must be a multiple of 8 in
range [0, 32760]`, demanding the immediate form `[reg, #imm]`.

`Prefetch::read` and `Prefetch::write` are pure performance hints;
omitting them is harmless. Skip the inline asm entirely under
`__CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__`. Phase 2 may reintroduce a cap-aware
`prfm` (use `prfum` or rewrite with `__builtin_prefetch`).

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0020)

--- a/src/hotspot/os_cpu/bsd_aarch64/prefetch_bsd_aarch64.inline.hpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/os_cpu/bsd_aarch64/prefetch_bsd_aarch64.inline.hpp
@@ -31,13 +31,17 @@


 inline void Prefetch::read (void *loc, intx interval) {
+#ifndef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
   if (interval >= 0)
     asm("prfm PLDL1KEEP, [%0, %1]" : : "r"(loc), "r"(interval));
+#endif
 }

 inline void Prefetch::write(void *loc, intx interval) {
+#ifndef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
   if (interval >= 0)
     asm("prfm PSTL1KEEP, [%0, %1]" : : "r"(loc), "r"(interval));
+#endif
 }

 #endif // OS_CPU_BSD_AARCH64_PREFETCH_BSD_AARCH64_INLINE_HPP
